    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>As you are chief magistrate of this city, and as such entrusted with the safety of
                all<lb/> the inhabitants, I trust that I do not presume too much by intruding on
                your time<lb/> which must be now fully occupied.</p>
            <p>You some weeks ago made a proclamation against mass violence, and it then had<lb/>
                occurred to me that I about have to complain of any threatened application
                toward<lb/> myself of this worse than Prussian tyranny. But the fact is so
                nevertheless. Yesterday<lb/> a certain lawyer <persName>M A Dropsie Esq.</persName>,
                whose name you perhaps know, said to me in the<lb/> course of some conversation
                referring to the important conflict now progressing: “You better take<lb/> care what
                you say; you are already on the <hi rend="underline">suspected</hi> list, and you
                may be compelled<lb/> to quit the city before long!” Now I know nothing of a <hi
                    rend="underline">legal</hi> or illegal suspected<lb/> list of the inhabitants of
                this city, nor am I conscious of any offense against the laws of this<lb/>
                corporation, or the constitution, or the laws of the State of the Union, why I
                should be suspected</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>of anything, much less why I should be ordered by anyone to quit
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.<lb/> You will therefore greatly oblige an
                old resident, who knew your grandfather<lb/> thirty years ago, whether such a
                suspected list is in existence, and if so,<lb/> for what cause my name was placed
                thereon; and if so whether I shall be<lb/> liable to a summary expulsion from this
                place; and that i may make on time<lb/> the necessary preparation, to go back to a
                country less free than this,<lb/> but where the people at least have the assurance,
                that they are not liable to be<lb/> molested by anyone, who in time of trouble may
                endeavor far more malice<add>?</add><lb/> to denounce them to an irresponsible power
                which being unknown to the law,<lb/> places the law &amp; common sense at
                defiance.</p>
            <p>It is useless to enlarge more on this matter, as the within is sufficient.<lb/> I
                make no formal complaint against <persName>Mr Dropsie</persName>, as I trust in the
                frank<lb/> assurance of the <persName>Mayor</persName> of
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> that he knows nothing of any charge
                against<lb/> me.    Re<hi rend="sup">y</hi></p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">IL</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <placeName>1227 W.</placeName>
                <date>June 3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> 1861</date>
            </p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Office of the Mayor</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>OF THE</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>CITY OF PHILADELPHIA</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>June 3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> 1861</date>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>No 1227 Walnut St.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Sir—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The contents of<lb/> your note of this morning<lb/> greatly astonish
                me.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I do not know why the<lb/> language of which you<lb/> complain
                should have been used by <persName>Mr. M. A. Dropsie.</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I can with pleasure<lb/> assure you that your loyalty<lb/> has never
                been impinged,<lb/> so far as I am aware—and<lb/> I have no knowledge of the<lb/>
                existence of a “suspected list”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am very Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">Alexander Henry</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
